sources.title: Drift Fence
sources.description: Jim Traft (Benny Baker) gets rodeo champ Travis (Tom Keene) to take his place as the new owner of a ranch having trouble with rustlers. To stop the rustling Travis and his men build a drift fence. Out to stop them is Clay Jackson (Stanley Andrews) and his men led by Slinger Dunn (Buster Crabbe).

sources.title: Drift Fence (1936) BUSTER CRABBEüçïZANE GREY
sources.description:
Stars: Buster Crabbe, Katherine DeMille, Tom Keene
Director: Otho Lovering
Story: Zane Grey

A cowboy pretends to be city dude sent to manage uncle's ranch, when he learns the ranch is being menaced by an outlaw who the cowboy badly wants to catch.
